// ===================================================================
// B MAJOR (anchor: RH root = 71 / B4, LH root = 59 / B3, matching "B Major" scale)
// B major's arpeggio LH uses finger 4 (not 5) whenever the LOWEST note of the run is
// the tonic (B) or the 5th degree (F#) — this mirrors the book's documented "4th
// finger lands on both the tonic and the 5th degree" quirk already used for this
// key's scale/root-position-arpeggio fingering (ground truth chart). Applied here
// to root position (bottom=B) and 2nd inversion (bottom=F#); 1st inversion's bottom
// note (D#) is unaffected and uses the standard 5. NOT extended to the dominant
// 7th arpeggio (no confirmation it applies there) — see review log.
// Dominant 7th built on F#, anchored a 4th below tonic (D7anchor = 66 / F#4).
// ===================================================================

