// ===================================================================
// D MINOR (anchor: RH root = 62 / D4, LH root = 50 / D3, matching "D Minor" scale)
// Triad uses D minor's own fingering family (RH 1,2,3,1,2,3,5 — same as majors;
// LH 5,4,2,1,4,2,1 — differs from majors' 5,3,2,1,3,2,1 because the minor 3rd
// shifts the middle finger from 3 to 4). All three positions are accidental-free
// (D-F-A triad), so this key has zero missing-audio gaps for the triad.
// Diminished 7th is built on the leading tone C#, anchored a half-step below
// tonic (DIM7anchor = 61 / C#4). Its 3rd inversion needs pc10 spelled "Bb" (not
// "As") to match D minor's own established flat-6th convention (Bb already used
// in this key's natural-minor scale).
// The book marks this key's root-position triad arpeggio "Play LH 8va" (printed
// LH written an octave from where it sounds) — that's a page-layout/print-space
// choice in the source book, not reflected in this app's MIDI pitches, which
// follow the app's own existing LH-anchor convention (RH - 12) instead. See
// review log.
// ===================================================================

